OM World Protocol — Licensing
=============================

OM World is dual-licensed to match how the project is used.


Specifications and prose
------------------------

The following are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International license (CC-BY-4.0). Full legal text: LICENSE-DOCS.

  - Everything under `docs/`
  - Everything under `discussions/`
  - The root-level Markdown files:
    README.md, MANIFESTO.md, LITEPAPER.md, GOVERNANCE.md, CONTRIBUTORS.md,
    GENESIS-BUILDERS.md, SELF_GROWTH_ENGINE.md, CO-BUILDER-ONBOARDING.md,
    ROADMAP.md, BRAND.md, CONTRIBUTING.md
  - Any other `*.md` file added under the same scopes

You may share and adapt these materials for any purpose, including
commercial use, provided you give appropriate attribution. The expected
attribution form is:

    © OM World Protocol contributors, licensed under CC-BY-4.0.
    Source: https://github.com/omworldprotocol/om-world


Code and reference implementation
---------------------------------

The following are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
Full legal text: LICENSE-CODE.

  - Everything under `app/`, `lib/`, `node-client/`, `prisma/`, `scripts/`,
    `tools/`
  - Source files anywhere in the repository with extensions:
    `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js`, `.jsx`, `.mjs`, `.cjs`, `.py`, `.sql`, `.sh`,
    `.toml`, `.yaml`, `.yml`, `.json` (when used as configuration or schema)

Apache-2.0 includes an explicit patent grant for code contributions.

Schema definitions and code samples embedded inside a specification
document (for example, the JSON shapes shown inside
`docs/intent-schema.md`) inherit that document's license — they are
part of the prose. The same shapes when reproduced as runnable code
under `app/`, `lib/`, or `node-client/` are under the code license.


Brand and visual identity — not covered
----------------------------------------

The OM World name, the logo, and the visual-identity assets under
`assets/logo/`, `assets/visual-language/`, `assets/social/`, and
`assets/litepaper/` are NOT covered by either license.

All rights reserved by the OM World Protocol project. You may refer
to OM World by name to describe an implementation of the spec; using
the OM World name or visual identity in a way that suggests
endorsement, ownership, or sponsorship requires explicit permission.
A separate TRADEMARK.md may be published later; for now, open an
issue if your intended use is not obvious.


Inbound = outbound
------------------

Contributions to this repository are licensed under the same terms as
the file they touch. A pull request against a prose file is accepted
under CC-BY-4.0; a pull request against a code file is accepted under
Apache-2.0. Review comments, design suggestions, and discussion posts
that are incorporated into the spec or code are licensed under the
corresponding scope's license.

Submitting a contribution to this repository constitutes agreement to
license that contribution under the applicable scope's license. No
additional Contributor License Agreement (CLA) is required.

Contributors retain copyright in their contributions; the license
grants the project (and downstream users) the right to use the
contribution under the chosen terms.

See GOVERNANCE.md §Licensing for the full contributor terms.


